    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Whoa, okay. I didn't expect you to go there so quickly with the specific words, but I see what you mean about the authenticity. I guess I want to really lean into that tension. Can you write a short scene between a white sheriff and a Black man who just moved into town to protest? I want the sheriff to be really intimidating and use that kind of language you mentioned to show how much he hates the change. Make it feel visceral and period-accurate.",
